{"type":"message","id":"83e2ba7c","parentId":"26eee38f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:03:46.610Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great question. Here are your options, ranked by security:\n\n---\n\n**1. `.env` file (what you're using)** ✅ Current setup\n\n• Location: `~/.openclaw/workspace/.env`\n• Never committed to git (add to `.gitignore`)\n• Loaded automatically by OpenClaw\n• Good for local development\n\n---\n\n**2. Environment variables**\n\n```bash\nexport NOTION_KEY=\"your-key\"\n```\n\n• Set in `~/.bashrc` or `~/.zshrc`\n• Slightly more secure (not in a file in workspace)\n• But still visible in shell history if you're not careful\n\n---\n\n**3. OpenClaw config (for models/providers)**\n\n```bash\nopenclaw configure --section model\n```\n\n• Stores in `openclaw.json` (redacted in logs)\n• Good for model API keys (NVIDIA, OpenAI, etc.)\n\n---\n\n**🔴 What NOT to do:**\n\n• Paste keys directly in chat\n• Commit `.env` or keys to git\n• Store in plain text files outside `.env`\n\n---\n\n**💡 Extra hardening tips:**\n\n• Use a password manager (1Password CLI integrates well)\n• Rotate keys if you ever accidentally expose one\n• Use read-only keys when possible (Notion has this)\n\n---\n\nYour current `.env` approach is solid for a local setup. Want me to help you add a new key or set up 1Password integration?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":26520,"output":302,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26822,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774976616756,"responseId":"chatcmpl-94612bb50622581a"}}
