{"type":"message","id":"92bcb638","parentId":"ac8a66f2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:10:59.022Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Honest answer: **moderately secure for local dev, but not bulletproof.** --- **What protects it:** • It's in your home directory (`~/.openclaw/workspace/`) • Not in a typical web root or shared location • OpenClaw redacts values in logs (`__OPENCLAW_REDACTED__`) • Can be gitignored easily --- **What doesn't protect it:** • It's a **plain text file** — anyone with file access can read it • Any app running as your user can read it • If you ever accidentally `cat` it in a screen share, it's exposed • Backup tools (Time Machine, rsync, etc.) may copy it • If your machine is compromised, it's one of the first places attackers look • Not encrypted at rest --- **Real-world risk level:** | Scenario | Risk | |----------|------| | Laptop stolen (encrypted drive) | Low if encrypted | | Malware on your machine | High — can read `.env` | | Accidental screen share | Medium | | Git push accident | High if not gitignored | | Shared computer | High | --- **Better alternatives for higher security:** 1. **1Password CLI + session injection** — keys stay in 1Password, injected only when needed 2. **Environment variables in shell** — slightly harder to accidentally expose 3. **Secrets manager** (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager) — overkill for solo dev --- **For your threat model (solo dev, local machine):** `.env` is **fine** for: • Notion, YouTube API keys (low damage if leaked) • Free-tier keys with usage limits **Not fine for:** • Production database passwords • Keys with billing attached (AWS, etc.) • Anything that could cost you money if abused --- Want me to show you the 1Password integration? It's the best balance of security and convenience."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":26865,"output":399,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27264,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774977036625,"responseId":"chatcmpl-90a0191be0c56c1a"}}
