{"type":"message","id":"d1ee25d6","parentId":"37e4111e","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:19:15.701Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Not set up yet.** You have the CLI, but need to: **Step 1: Enable in 1Password desktop app** 1. Open 1Password app 2. Go to **Settings → Security** → enable system authentication (Linux auth) 3. Go to **Developer → Settings** → check **\"Integrate with 1Password CLI\"** **Step 2: Sign in** Once the app integration is on: ```bash op signin ``` It will use your system authentication (fingerprint/password) instead of storing credentials. --- Want me to walk you through storing your first API key in 1Password once you've enabled the integration?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"z-ai/glm5","usage":{"input":27668,"output":138,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27806,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774977548941,"responseId":"chatcmpl-9f38d6518c4f41d0"}}
