{"type":"message","id":"bb5f1e2c","parentId":"1a6ebc77","timestamp":"2026-03-31T17:20:20.523Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me clarify the current state and how 1Password integration works with OpenClaw.\n\n**Current Status:**\n- 1Password CLI is installed (`/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin/op` v2.33.1)\n- Not authenticated (`op whoami` shows \"no account found for filter\")\n- Desktop app integration likely not enabled (would need to be for seamless auth)\n\n**How it works (once fully set up):**\n\n1. **Desktop App Setup (one-time):**\n   - Open 1Password app → Settings → Security → Enable system authentication (Linux auth)\n   - Settings → Developer → Check \"Integrate with 1Password CLI\"\n   - This allows CLI to use your system auth (fingerprint/password) instead of master password\n\n2. **Sign in to CLI:**\n   ```bash\n   op signin\n   ```\n   - Uses your system authentication (no secrets stored in shell history or plaintext)\n   - Creates an encrypted session token in memory (expires after 30 minutes of inactivity)\n\n3. **Retrieve secrets (when needed):**\n   ```bash\n   op read \"op://Vault/Item/field\"\n   ```\n   - Example: `op read \"op://Personal/NOTION_KEY/password\"`\n   - Returns just the secret value, nothing more\n   - Secret lives only in memory during the command execution\n\n4. **OpenClaw Integration:**\n   - There's a 1Password skill in your workspace\n   - Can use `message` tool with `action=send` to run `op read` commands via exec\n   - Or create subagents that use 1Password CLI with injected secrets\n   - Secret never touches OpenClaw's config or logs (redacted)\n\n**Benefits vs .env:**\n- No plaintext secrets on disk (vault is encrypted)\n- Automatic locking when 1Password locks or times out\n- Biometric/system auth protection\n- Easy rotation: change in vault, all apps get update\n- Audit trails in 1Password\n- Can share specific items with team members if needed\n\n**For your current keys:**\n- NOTION_KEY and YOUTUBE_KEY could move to 1Password\n- Would keep your workspace cleaner\n- Adds protection against accidental exposure\n\n**Want to proceed?** I can:\n1. Guide you through enabling the desktop app integration\n2. Help you sign in to the CLI\n3. Show how to migrate your first key (NOTION_KEY) to 1Password\n4. Demonstrate reading it in OpenClaw\n\nOr if you prefer sticking with .env for now (totally fine for low-risk keys), just say the word","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Not set up for authentication yet, but"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":".\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" here's how it works:\n\n**Current status:**\n- ✅ 1Password CLI installed (v2.33.1)\n- ❌ Not signed in (`op whoami` shows \"no account found\")\n- ❌ Desktop app integration likely not enabled\n\n**How it works (once configured):**\n\n1. **Enable in 1Password app (one-time):**\n   - Open 1Password → Settings → Security → Enable **Linux system auth**\n   - Settings → Developer → Check **\"Integrate with 1Password CLI\"**\n   - This lets CLI use your system authentication (fingerprint/password)\n\n2. **Sign in to CLI:**\n   ```bash\n   op signin\n   ```\n   - Uses your system auth (no master password typed, nothing in shell history)\n   - Creates encrypted session token in memory (expires after 30min idle)\n\n3. **Retrieve secrets (when needed):**\n   ```bash\n   op read \"op://Vault/Item/field\"\n   ```\n   - Example: `op read \"op://Personal/NOTION_KEY/password\"`\n   - Returns only the secret value\n   - Secret lives only in memory during command execution\n\n4. **OpenClaw integration:**\n   - There's a 1Password skill in your workspace\n   - Can use `message` tool to run `op read` via `exec`\n   - Or create subagents that use 1Password CLI with injected secrets\n   - **Secret never touches OpenClaw's config or logs** (automatically redacted)\n\n**Benefits vs .env:**\n- No plaintext secrets on disk (vault is AES-256 encrypted)\n- Automatic locking when 1Password locks or times out\n- Biometric/system auth protection (fingerprint, face ID, system password)\n- Easy rotation: change in vault, all apps get update\n- Audit trails in 1Password\n- Can share specific items with team if needed\n\n**For your keys:**\n- NOTION_KEY and YOUTUBE_KEY could move to 1Password\n- Would keep your workspace cleaner\n- Adds defense-in-depth against accidental exposure\n\n**Want to proceed?** I can guide you through:\n1. Enabling the desktop app integration\n2. Signing in to the CLI\n3. Migrating your first key to 1Password\n4. Demonstrating reading it in OpenClaw\n\nOr if you prefer sticking with .env for now (totally fine for low-risk keys like Notion/YouTube), just say the word."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":35467,"output":1102,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":36569,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774977575763,"responseId":"chatcmpl-a1337136a11631c2"}}
