s per the rules: \"Before answering anything about prior work, decisions, dates, people, preferences, or todos: run memory_search on MEMORY.md + memory/*.md\"\n\nBut the user just said \"/start\", which isn't really asking about prior work. It's more like a command to start.\n\nI think the best approach is to respond friendly and ask what they need help with, following my persona.\n\nLet me craft a response: Hey Ivek! 👋 Welcome back. What would you like to work on today?\n\nBut I should check if there are any updates in memory or anything urgent.\n\nActually, let me quickly check the memory file for today to see if there's anything new.\n\nI already read memory/2026-03-31.md earlier and it didn't exist (error). But maybe it was created since then? Let me check.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4e08aa00ff654aaabf6cdd66","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ivo/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-31.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":28167,"output":663,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774983853058,"responseId":"chatcmpl-81dfc7c376214525"}}
