{"type":"message","id":"f4eda6ce","parentId":"c7bb6e48","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:17:27.026Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d7b1ef16ca8d4124b983003a","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"Step 2 of the OpenClaw setup guide is **Sub-agent Configuration** [1]. \\n\\nThis step focuses on how to properly set up your **\\\"main brain\\\" model** to work alongside cheaper **\\\"muscle agents\\\"** so they can function together as a team [1]. According to the sources, this is a critical part of the process because OpenClaw frequently breaks if this specific configuration is handled incorrectly [1]. By coordinating these models, you can ensure they work together smoothly without compromising the system's stability [1].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"laid it out so you can jump to any section. You don't have to watch this in order. So we have about 23 chapters covered in this course. Let's take a quick look. Chapter one is installation and setup. This is the fastest setup you'll find, plus how to get up to $1,500 in free API credits across AWS, Google Cloud, and Azure OpenAI. Chapter 2, sub-agent configuration. How to set up your main brain model and cheaper muzzle agents so they work together without breaking your configuration. Trust me, open clock breaks when you do this wrong. I'll show you the right way.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quiet-shoal","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"Step 2 of the OpenClaw setup guide is **Sub-agent Configuration** [1]. \\n\\nThis step focuses on how to properly set up your **\\\"main brain\\\" model** to work alongside cheaper **\\\"muscle agents\\\"** so they can function together as a team [1]. According to the sources, this is a critical part of the process because OpenClaw frequently breaks if this specific configuration is handled incorrectly [1]. By coordinating these models, you can ensure they work together smoothly without compromising the system's stability [1].\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    },\n    \"references\": [\n      {\n        \"source_id\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n        \"citation_number\": 1,\n        \"cited_text\": \"laid it out so you can jump to any section. You don't have to watch this in order. So we have about 23 chapters covered in this course. Let's take a quick look. Chapter one is installation and setup. This is the fastest setup you'll find, plus how to get up to $1,500 in free API credits across AWS, Google Cloud, and Azure OpenAI. Chapter 2, sub-agent configuration. How to set up your main brain model and cheaper muzzle agents so they work together without breaking your configuration. Trust me, open clock breaks when you do this wrong. I'll show you the right way.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n","name":"nlm notebook"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774984647023}}
