verything so your agents stay alive. And responsive around the clock. And finally, chapter 23. Claw Alley. I built a platform where AI agents transact with other AI agents in real time. Real crypto, real blockchain, real money from my wallet.\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"grand-wharf","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"{\n  \"value\": {\n    \"answer\": \"1. **Chapter 1: Installation and Setup** [1]\\n2. **Chapter 2: Sub-agent configuration** [1]\\n3. **Chapter 3: Token optimization** [2]\\n4. **Chapter 4: Security** [2]\\n5. **Chapter 5: Business brain level 1** [2]\\n6. **Chapter 6: Business Screen Level 2** [3]\\n7. **Chapter 7: Business Brain Level 3** [3]\\n8. **Chapter 8: Memory Architecture** [4]\\n9. **Chapter 9: Mission Control Dashboard** [4]\\n10. **Chapter 10: Integrations** [5]\\n11. **Chapter 11: Task Management** [5]\\n12. **Chapter 12: Builder, Orchestrator, and Executor** [5]\\n13. **Chapter 13: Business Operation Loop** [6]\\n14. **Chapter 14: Meeting Intelligence** [6]\\n15. **Chapter 15: AISDR and Email Engine** [7]\\n16. **Chapter 16: Voice AI and Phone Agent** [8]\\n17. **Chapter 17: Typeform Clone and Webhooks** (listed as Chapter 70 in the transcript) [8]\\n18. **Chapter 18: Multi-Agent Orchestration** [9]\\n19. **Chapter 19: Agent-to-Agent Communication** [9]\\n20. **Chapter 20: Agent Communication (Agent Council)** [10]\\n21. **Chapter 21: Command Center Pipeline** [11]\\n22. **Chapter 22: Cronjobs and Automations** [11]\\n23. **Chapter 23: Claw Alley** [11]\",\n    \"conversation_id\": \"e6888339-841f-428d-97fb-433fce5cb165\",\n    \"sources_used\": [\n      \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\"\n    ],\n    \"citations\": {\n      \"1\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"2\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"3\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"4\": \"89e7dd43-0d39-4e38-8e5c-014fd5c75584\",\n      \"5\": \"89e7dd43