r, coder, voice handler).  \n- **Token optimization:** 8-layer stack (main brain → muscle → isolation → role scoping → tool limits → concurrency → memory/auth isolation).  \n\n### 🔍 Next Checks (before we execute)\n1. Confirm GLM5 reasoning is on (we can check with a quick test or `/reasoning` status).  \n2. Pick 1–2 muscle agents to start with (e.g., Kimi K 2.5 for daily ops, DeepSeek V3.2 for research).  \n3. Define the first subagent we’ll spawn (e.g., a “researcher” using DeepSeek V3.2).  \n\n### 📋 Your Call\nDoes this match what you saw in the notebook for Step 2?  \nWant to tweak any model choices or roles before we finalize the plan?  \n\nOnce you say “go,” we’ll move to execution — but for now, it’s all planning.  \n\nWhat do you think? 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":90943,"output":658,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":91601,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774986203129,"responseId":"chatcmpl-8a4d55442f84d059"}}
