{"type":"message","id":"cc6454c0","parentId":"119c1173","timestamp":"2026-03-31T19:54:25.828Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We are still in planning mode for Step 2. The user has indicated:\n- Main brain: GLM5 (check reasoning enabled)\n- Muscle agents: DeepSeek V3.2 for coding, Kimi K 2.5 for daily ops\n- Also mentioned: Nemotron 3 Super is amazing as a generalist with enormous context and follows instructions well.\n\nWe need to finalize the plan. Let's decide on the roles:\n\nOption 1: Use GLM5 as main brain (planner/reasoner), DeepSeek V3.2 as coder, Kimi K 2.5 for daily ops/research, and maybe Nemotron 3 Super as an alternative generalist or for specific tasks.\n\nBut the notebook emphasizes having a main brain and muscle agents. The main brain should be the one doing high-level reasoning and coordination. The user originally said they want to use GLM5 as main brain and check if reasoning is enabled.\n\nWe also have the system prompt default model as Nemotron, but the user wants to use GLM5 for main brain.\n\nLet's confirm: The user wants to set up sub-agent configuration with GLM5 as the main brain. We should verify that reasoning is working for GLM5.\n\nWe can do a quick test after we finalize the plan, but for now, we are still planning.\n\nLet's propose the following plan for Step 2:\n\n**Step 2: Sub-agent Configuration Plan**\n1. Set main brain model to GLM5 and verify reasoning is enabled.\n2. Assign muscle agents:\n   - DeepSeek V3.2 for coding tasks\n   - Kimi K 2.5 for daily operations, research, and long-context tasks\n   - (Optional) Nemotron 3 Super as a fallback generalist or for specific high-reasoning tasks if needed, but we want to keep the main brain as GLM5 to avoid overloading it.\n3. Use sub-agent isolation (forward slash spawn) for each muscle agent to ensure clean context.\n4. Define roles: \n   - Main brain (GLM5): Planner, coordinator, high-level reasoning.\n   - DeepSeek V3.2: Coder, developer,